Embraer adheres to its delivering forecasts for 2008 
The Brazilian aircraft manufacturer expects 215 delivered airplanes despite the threatening recession as danger for the world economy this year. 
The president Fredrico Fleury Curado confirmed the fourth largest aircraft manufacturer of the world adheres, Embraer, to his delivering forecasts for 2008 with 215 delivered airplanes. 
The aircraft manufacturer delivered 97 airplanes in the first six months. 
The Brazilian manufacturer hopes for much of the Chinese market primarily for his airplanes of the range of 30 to 120 seats. 
Embraer has delivered 41 machines to Chinese customers within eight years to this day. 
